name: Rufous-necked Hornbill
rangeDescription: Himalayan foothills to southwestern china and northern southeastern asia
description: Large hornbill with broad dark grooves on the upper mandible. Male has rufous head, neck, and underparts; female is all black.

name: Orange Bullfinch
rangeDescription: Montane forest of northern pakistan to northwestern india (himachal pradesh)
description: A small, brightly colored bullfinch. The male is orange with black mask, wings, and tail.

name: Vogelkop Owlet-nightjar
description: A mid-sized owlet-nightjar of lower montane forests. Strongly barred back and chest with a brown base, whitish belly and a pale collar.

name: Salim Ali's Swift
rangeDescription: Eastern tibetan plateau, western sichuan; winter range unknown
description: A large scimitar-winged swift of valleys, cliffs, and gorges. Nests in buildings and rock crevices; often gives a chattering scream when entering and leaving the nest.

name: Cassin's Spinetail
rangeDescription: Sierra leone and liberia to northwestern angola and western uganda; bioko
description: A distinctive swift of lowland forest that appears nearly tailless. The wings appear “pinched” at the body but are otherwise fairly straight and broad.
